This validation serves more as a sensibility#todo[right word?] test than a true validation of thermal comfort along the routes. The validation aims to show that the thermally comfortable routes are notably different from the shortest path; in distance and average temperature. But also that the algorithm behaves in a predictable way for different types of routes. However, due to the levels of abstraction a true validation of thermal comfort would most likely require actual human participation to walk along the routes. Which is outside the scope of this research.#todo[should be discussion maybe?]
